column5: We are headed up to Lac Suel this Saturday 7/31. Looking for a good place that's reasonably priced to eat lunch on the way, possibly in Nestor Falls or Sioux Narrows. Any Suggestions? 3 days and on our way to Fisherman's Cove Resort, Lac Seul! Thanks! RBF

One of the restaurants we stop at for breakfast on the way up is in Nestor Falls, it's called LOG CAYBIN. It opens at 6 am and always has good food I think. I would bet it serves a delicious lunch too. Prices aren't too bad either. Have a fun week !iowa jal
I second the Log Cabin. It's owned by a really nice young lady named Monique who serves LARGE portions well cooked. If you like their lunch...you should see their breakfast.
The Rod & Reel in Souix Narrows right north of the bridge would be a candidate, we've eaten lunch there several times.
Thanks for the suggestions, we will try them out. RBF
